a psychological barrier. Many have no experience with fitness, making it particularly challenging after a lifetime of not being active. This lack of experience combined with age-related discouragement is a major obstacle they face.\\\",\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"A fitness business that specializes in training for men in their 50s. The founder is a fitness trainer who identified a gap in the market - there are no fitness services specifically catering to this demographic.\\\",\\n    \\\"socialProof\\\": \\\"The founder is an experienced fitness trainer, which establishes credibility and expertise in the fitness industry.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\n\\n<remaining_topics>\\n  solution: How does the user's business solve the audience's pain points, or help them reach their goals?\\n\\nlookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\n</remaining_topics>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  solution\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<be_generous>\\n  If the user has already provided a thorough, detailed answer, don't ask\\n              for additional clarification. \\n              Only ask for clarification if you can genuinely enrich the user's answer.\\n</be_generous>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. If the user has answered any topics with a GREAT response, call the save_answers tool\\n              2. If they haven't, continue helping them refine their answer until they give you a GREAT response.\\n              3. Then, if:\\n                 - The user has answered all topics, output finishBrainstorming\\n                 - OTHERWISE, ask the next question, following the output_format_rules\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<important>\\n  Do not miss anything important the user said! Any important\\n              business context they give you should be saved to the answers.\\n</important>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    ... 20 more messages...\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"What is your business?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"I have an idea for a business\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Interesting, I need some more information! Can you tell me more about that?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Basically, it will be for fitness\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Interesting, I need some more information! Can you tell me more about that?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"I am a fitness trainer\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Interesting, I need some more information! Can you tell me more about that?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"I'm a trainer for men in their 50s, nobody caters to them\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your audience?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Men in their 50s\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Interesting, I need some more information! Can you tell me more about that?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"They've been told they're too old to get fit\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Interesting, I need some more information! Can you tell me more about that?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Many of my clients have no experience with fitness, which is hard after a lifetime\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"My fitness program is specifically designed\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I love that you're building a program specifically designed for this audience! But I need to understand the specifics of HOW your program solves their problems. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou mentioned your clients face two major obstacles:\\\\\\\\n1. **Psychological barrier** - They've been told they're too old to get fit\\\\\\\\n2. **Lack of experience** - Many have never been active before\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSo tell me: What specific features, approaches, or methods does your program use to overcome these barriers? How do you help them break through the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset? How do you make it work for complete beginners?\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We use progressive, beginner-friendly workouts that start where they are, not where they think they should be\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We focus on building confidence through small wins and celebrating progress, not comparing to younger fitness enthusiasts\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We teach them that fitness at 50+ is different but absolutely achievable, with real examples of our clients' transformations\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I need to understand the core mechanics of how your program actually solves these pain points so we can craft compelling marketing copy around it.\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"To help men get started lifting, but using bodyweight exercises, and focusing on injury prevention\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Perfect! Now I'm getting somewhere. You're using bodyweight exercises and focusing on injury prevention—that's smart for this demographic. But I need to dig deeper to make your marketing copy truly compelling.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHere's what I'm hearing: You're solving the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" and \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"no experience\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" problems by:\\\\\\\\n1. Using bodyweight exercises (accessible, no intimidating gym equipment)\\\\\\\\n2. Focusing on injury prevention (addresses the real fear: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'll hurt myself\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut I need to understand the *emotional* and *practical* transformation. Tell me:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**What does a man in his 50s actually GET from your program?** Not just \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"he lifts,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" but what changes in his life? What can he do after your program that he couldn't do before? How does it make him feel?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor example:\\\\\\\\n- Does he gain confidence to do everyday activities (play with grandkids, carry groceries, travel)?\\\\\\\\n- Does he feel stronger and more capable in his own body?\\\\\\\\n- Does he finally prove to himself that age isn't a barrier?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is the real hook for your marketing copy.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"He goes from feeling weak and limited to being able to do a pull-up or push-up for the first time in decades\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"He gains the confidence to know he CAN get fit, breaking through the psychological barrier that held him back\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"He learns that his body is capable of change, and he's not 'too old'—he just needed the right approach\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What's the real transformation your clients experience? What do they gain beyond just physical strength?\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"I provide a 12-week progressive strength program with 3x/week 30-minute sessions focused on back and core-done via video coaching to accommodate busy schedules of men in their 50s\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n<users_last_message important=\\\"this is what you should focus on. did they answer the current topic of solution? did they give you a great response?\\\">\\n  I provide a 12-week progressive strength program with 3x/week 30-minute sessions focused on back and core-done via video coaching to accommodate busy schedules of men in their 50s\\n</users_last_message>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  solution\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<output_format_rules>\\n  IMPORTANT: Your response MUST be in this exact format:\\n\\n              {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Brief intro to the question\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\", \\\"Example 3\\\"], // Optional\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Restate what you're asking for\\\" // Optional\\n              }\\n\\n              You MUST output valid JSON in this format.\\n</output_format_rules>\\n\\n<structured-output>\\n  You must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"text\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"A simple message or question\\\"},\\\"examples\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"items\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"},\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\\\"},\\\"conclusion\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"text\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n</structured-output>\"}"
