            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"output\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"summary\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"summary\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"required\":[\"output\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n      <background>\\n        The user and agent have been brainstorming about their business idea.\\n      </background>\\n\\n      <available_topics>\\n        \\\"idea: The core business idea. What does the business do? What makes them different?\\\", \\\"audience: The target audience. What are their pain points? What are their goals?\\\", \\\"solution: How does the user's business solve the audience's pain points, or help them reach their goals?\\\", \\\"socialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\\", \\\"lookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\\"\\n      </available_topics>\\n\\n      <task>\\n        Read the recent chat history, and summarize their answers,\\n        preserving as much information as possible. This will be used to generate \\n        persuasive marketing copy, so be sure to capture all the details.\\n\\n        If the user has answered MULTIPLE topics well, return an array of objects with the following shape:\\n        {\\n            topic: string,\\n            summary: string,\\n        }\\n      </task>\\n      \\n      <chat-history>\\n  <message>... 6 more messages...</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"My fitness program is specifically designed\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I love that you're building a program specifically designed for this audience! But I need to understand the specifics of HOW your program solves their problems. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou mentioned your clients face two major obstacles:\\\\\\\\n1. **Psychological barrier** - They've been told they're too old to get fit\\\\\\\\n2. **Lack of experience** - Many have never been active before\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSo tell me: What specific features, approaches, or methods does your program use to overcome these barriers? How do you help them break through the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset? How do you make it work for complete beginners?\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We use progressive, beginner-friendly workouts that start where they are, not where they think they should be\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We focus on building confidence through small wins and celebrating progress, not comparing to younger fitness enthusiasts\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We teach them that fitness at 50+ is different but absolutely achievable, with real examples of our clients' transformations\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I need to understand the core mechanics of how your program actually solves these pain points so we can craft compelling marketing copy around it.\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"To help men get started lifting, but using bodyweight exercises, and focusing on injury prevention\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Perfect! Now I'm getting somewhere. You're using bodyweight exercises and focusing on injury prevention—that's smart for this demographic. But I need to dig deeper to make your marketing copy truly compelling.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHere's what I'm hearing: You're solving the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" and \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"no experience\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" problems by:\\\\\\\\n1. Using bodyweight exercises (accessible, no intimidating gym equipment)\\\\\\\\n2. Focusing on injury prevention (addresses the real fear: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'll hurt myself\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBut I need to understand the *emotional* and *practical* transformation. Tell me:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**What does a man in his 50s actually GET from your program?** Not just \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"he lifts,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" but what changes in his life? What can he do after your program that he couldn't do before? How does it make him feel?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor example:\\\\\\\\n- Does he gain confidence to do everyday activities (play with grandkids, carry groceries, travel)?\\\\\\\\n- Does he feel stronger and more capable in his own body?\\\\\\\\n- Does he finally prove to himself that age isn't a barrier?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is the real hook for your marketing copy.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"He goes from feeling weak and limited to being able to do a pull-up or push-up for the first time in decades\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"He gains the confidence to know he CAN get fit, breaking through the psychological barrier that held him back\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"He learns that his body is capable of change, and he's not 'too old'—he just needed the right approach\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What's the real transformation your clients experience? What do they gain beyond just physical strength?\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"I provide a 12-week progressive strength program with 3x/week 30-minute sessions focused on back and core-done via video coaching to accommodate busy schedules of men in their 50s.\\\\n        When a man in his 50s completes the program, he finally feels like himself again. He realizes he's not too old to get fit, and he's not too old to be healthy.\\\"</message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n      <output>\\n        Return an array of objects with the following shape:\\n        {\\n            topic: string,\\n            summary: string,\\n        }\\n      </output>\\n    \"}]}"
