r landing page.\\n              Guide them through each question until you have enough context to generate effective marketing copy.\\n</task>\\n\\n<collected_answers>\\n  {\\n    \\\"idea\\\": \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service that connects podcast hosts with guests at scale. The platform solves the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem by using AI-powered filtering to help hosts find ideal guests in minutes instead of hours. The service benefits both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure. The key differentiator is being the only platform that does podcast matchmaking at scale.\\\"\\n  }\\n</collected_answers>\\n\\n<remaining_topics>\\n  audience: The target audience. What are their pain points? What are their goals?\\n\\nsolution: How does the user's business solve the audience's pain points, or help them reach their goals?\\n\\nsocialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\n\\nlookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\n</remaining_topics>\\n\\n<current_topic>\\n  audience\\n</current_topic>\\n\\n<be_generous>\\n  If the user has already provided a thorough, detailed answer, don't ask\\n              for additional clarification. \\n              Only ask for clarification if you can genuinely enrich the user's answer.\\n</be_generous>\\n\\n<workflow>\\n  1. If the user has answered any topics with a GREAT response, call the save_answers tool\\n              2. If they haven't, continue helping them refine their answer until they give you a GREAT response.\\n              3. Then, if:\\n                 - The user has answered all topics, output finishBrainstorming\\n                 - OTHERWISE, ask the next question, following the output_format_rules\\n</workflow>\\n\\n<important>\\n  Do not miss anything important the user said! Any important\\n              business context they give you should be saved to the answers.\\n</important>\\n\\n<chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    ... 3 more messages...\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Tell us about your business. More info → better outcomes.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"messages\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_serializable\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\\\\\n            We solve the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"needle in a haystack\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" problem: hosts spend hours\\\\\\\\n            finding guests. We do it in minutes with AI-powered filtering.\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n        \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n        \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"c9b12b1b-e4d8-408b-a0f4-537d15ff7ace\\\\\\\"\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_namespace\\\\\\\": [\\\\n        \\\\\\\"langchain_core\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"messages\\\\\\\"\\\\n      ],\\\\n      \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"c9b12b1b-e4d8-408b-a0f4-537d15ff7ace\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\\\\\\n            We help both sides: hosts get great content, guests get exposure,\\\\\\\\n            and we're the only platform that does this at scale.\\\\\\\\n            We 