            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "params": [],
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"output\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"topic\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"summary\":{\"type\":\"string\"}},\"required\":[\"topic\",\"summary\"],\"additionalProperties\":false}}},\"required\":[\"output\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n      <background>\\n        The user and agent have been brainstorming about their business idea.\\n      </background>\\n\\n      <available_topics>\\n        \\\"idea: The core business idea. What does the business do? What makes them different?\\\", \\\"audience: The target audience. What are their pain points? What are their goals?\\\", \\\"solution: How does the user's business solve the audience's pain points, or help them reach their goals?\\\", \\\"socialProof: Social proof or testimonials to include on the landing page. Remember, anything can be social proof: the user's background, experience, beliefs, founder story, etc.\\\", \\\"lookAndFeel: The look and feel of the landing page.\\\"\\n      </available_topics>\\n\\n      <task>\\n        Read the recent chat history, and summarize their answers,\\n        preserving as much information as possible. This will be used to generate \\n        persuasive marketing copy, so be sure to capture all the details.\\n\\n        If the user has answered MULTIPLE topics well, return an array of objects with the following shape:\\n        {\\n            topic: string,\\n            summary: string,\\n        }\\n      </task>\\n      \\n      <chat-history>\\n  <message>... 6 more messages...</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"That's awesome! And what about your solution?\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"My fitness program is specifically designed\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I love that you're building a program specifically designed for this audience! But I need to understand the specifics of HOW your program solves their problems. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou mentioned your clients face two major obstacles:\\\\\\\\n1. **Psychological barrier** - They've been told they're too old to get fit\\\\\\\\n2. **Lack of experience** - Many have never been active before\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSo tell me: What specific features, methods, or approaches does your program use to overcome these barriers? How do you help them break through the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset? How do you make it work for complete beginners?\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We use modified exercises that prove age is just a number, combined with motivational coaching that rebuilds their confidence\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We start with foundational movements and gradually progress, so beginners never feel overwhelmed or out of place\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"We focus on functional fitness that helps them with everyday activities, so they see real-world results immediately\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What makes your program different and specifically effective for men in their 50s with no fitness experience?\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"To help men get started lifting, but using bodyweight exercises, and focusing on injury prevention\\\"</message>\\n  <message>assistant: \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Great! So your solution focuses on bodyweight exercises and injury prevention. But I want to make sure we capture the FULL power of what you're offering.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou've told me WHAT you do (bodyweight exercises, injury prevention), but I need to understand the deeper impact. Let me ask you this:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**How does this specifically address the two pain points your clients face?**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n1. **The \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset** - How do bodyweight exercises and injury prevention help them overcome this psychological barrier? What results or confidence do they gain?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n2. **The beginner experience** - Why is bodyweight training + injury prevention the RIGHT approach for someone who's never been active? What makes them feel capable and successful?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn other words: What transformation or outcome do your clients experience? What can they DO or FEEL after working with you that they couldn't before?\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"They realize they can do real strength training without needing a gym, which removes the intimidation factor and proves age doesn't matter\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"They build strength safely without joint pain, so they actually stick with it and see results instead of getting injured and quitting\\\\\\\",\\\\n    \\\\\\\"They gain confidence through small wins with bodyweight movements, which rebuilds their belief that they CAN get fit\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What's the real transformation or benefit your clients experience from your bodyweight + injury prevention approach?\\\\\\\"\\\\n}\\\"</message>\\n  <message>human: \\\"I provide a 12-week progressive strength program with 3x/week 30-minute sessions focused on back and core-done via video coaching to accommodate busy schedules of men in their 50s.\\\\n        When a man in his 50s completes the program, he finally feels like himself again. He realizes he's not too old to get fit, and he's not too old to be healthy.\\\"</message>\\n</chat-history>\\n\\n      <output>\\n        Return an array of objects with the following shape:\\n        {\\n            topic: string,\\n            summary: string,\\n        }\\n      </output>\\n    \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1904,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1904,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_011nWKvLgMAu5mCfN3FibMeu\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01PGXaVAyDHNPhSU2TbTWrDA\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"output\":[{\"topic\":\"audience\",\"summary\":\"Men in their 50s who want to get fit but face two major obstacles: (1) a psychological barrier - they've been told they're too old to get fit, and (2) lack of experience - many have never been active before. They have busy schedules and need flexible, time-efficient solutions.\"},{\"topic\":\"solution\",\"summary\":\"A 12-week progressive strength program with 3 sessions per week, 30-minute sessions each. The program uses bodyweight exercises with a focus on injury prevention, specifically targeting back and core strength. Delivered via video coaching to accommodate busy schedules. The transformation clients experience: they feel like themselves again, realize they're not too old to get fit, and discover they're not too old to be healthy. The bodyweight approach removes gym intimidation, the injury prevention focus ensures they can stick with it without pain, and the progressive structure builds confidence through small wins.\"},{\"topic\":\"idea\",\"summary\":\"A fitness program specifically designed for men in their 50s to help them get started with strength training using bodyweight exercises and injury prevention as core pillars. What makes it different: it's tailored for beginners with no fitness experience, uses accessible bodyweight movements (no gym required), emphasizes safety and injury prevention, and is delivered in short, manageable video sessions that fit busy lifestyles.\"}]}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1861,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":361,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
