\\\"examples\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"We use modified exercises that prove age is just a number, combined with motivational coaching that rebuilds their confidence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"We start with foundational movements and gradually progress, so beginners never feel overwhelmed or out of place\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"We focus on functional fitness that helps them with everyday activities, so they see real-world results immediately\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n  ],\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"What makes your program different and specifically effective for men in their 50s with no fitness experience?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"topics\\\\\\\": [\\\\n          \\\\\\\"audience\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"solution\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"idea\\\\\\\"\\\\n        ]\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I love that you're building a program specifically designed for this audience! But I need to understand the specifics of HOW your program solves their problems. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou mentioned your clients face two major obstacles:\\\\\\\\n1. **Psychological barrier** - They've been told they're too old to get fit\\\\\\\\n2. **Lack of experience** - Many have never been active before\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSo tell me: What specific features, methods, or approaches does your program use to overcome these barriers? How do you help them break through the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset? How do you make it work for complete beginners?\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n          \\\\\\\"We use modified exercises that prove age is just a number, combined with motivational coaching that rebuilds their confidence\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"We start with foundational movements and gradually progress, so beginners never feel overwhelmed or out of place\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"We focus on functional fitness that helps them with everyday activities, so they see real-world results immediately\\\\\\\"\\\\n        ],\\\\n        \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What makes your program different and specifically effective for men in their 50s with no fitness experience?\\\\\\\"\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"ai\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"tool_calls\\\\\\\": [],\\\\n      \\\\\\\"invalid_tool_calls\\\\\\\": []\\\\n    },\\\\n    {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_serializable\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"To help men get started lifting, but using bodyweight exercises, and focusing on injury prevention\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n        \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n        \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"83e6790b-842b-4120-a665-bef37ea2f694\\\\\\\"\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_namespace\\\\\\\": [\\\\n        \\\\\\\"langchain_core\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"messages\\\\\\\"\\\\n      ],\\\\n      \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"83e6790b-842b-4120-a665-bef37ea2f694\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"To help men get started lifting, but using bodyweight exercises, and focusing on injury prevention\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"topics\\\\\\\": [\\\\n          \\\\\\\"audience\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"solution\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"idea\\\\\\\"\\\\n        ]\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n      \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"human\\\\\\\"\\\\n    },\\\\n    {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_serializable\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Great! So your solution focuses on bodyweight exercises and injury prevention. But I want to make sure we capture the FULL power of what you're offering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nYou've told me WHAT you do (bodyweight exercises, injury prevention), but I need to understand the deeper impact. Let me ask you this:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**How does this specifically address the two pain points your clients face?**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. **The \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset** - How do bodyweight exercises and injury prevention help them overcome this psychological barrier? What results or confidence do they gain?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. **The beginner experience** - Why is bodyweight training + injury prevention the RIGHT approach for someone who's never been active? What makes them feel capable and successful?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nIn other words: What transformation or outcome do your clients experience? What can they DO or FEEL after working with you that they couldn't before?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"They realize they can do real strength training without needing a gym, which removes the intimidation factor and proves age doesn't matter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"They build strength safely without joint pain, so they actually stick with it and see results instead of getting injured and quitting\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"They gain confidence through small wins with bodyweight movements, which rebuilds their belief that they CAN get fit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n  ],\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"What's the real transformation or benefit your clients experience from your bodyweight + injury prevention approach?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {\\\\n          \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Great! So your solution focuses on bodyweight exercises and injury prevention. But I want to make sure we capture the FULL power of what you're offering.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou've told me WHAT you do (bodyweight exercises, injury prevention), but I need to understand the deeper impact. Let me ask you this:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**How does this specifically address the two pain points your clients face?**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n1. **The \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset** - How do bodyweight exercises and injury prevention help them overcome this psychological barrier? What results or confidence do they gain?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n2. **The beginner experience** - Why is bodyweight training + injury prevention the RIGHT approach for someone who's never been active? What makes them feel capable and successful?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn other words: What transformation or outcome do your clients experience? What can they DO or FEEL after working with you that they couldn't before?\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n            \\\\\\\"They realize they can do real strength training without needing a gym, which removes the intimidation factor and proves age doesn't matter\\\\\\\",\\\\n            \\\\\\\"They build strength safely without joint pain, so they actually stick with it and see results instead of getting injured and quitting\\\\\\\",\\\\n            \\\\\\\"They gain confidence through small wins with bodyweight movements, which rebuilds their belief that they CAN get fit\\\\\\\"\\\\n          ],\\\\n          \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What's the real transformation or benefit your clients experience from your bodyweight + injury prevention approach?\\\\\\\"\\\\n        },\\\\n        \\\\\\\"tool_calls\\\\\\\": [],\\\\n        \\\\\\\"invalid_tool_calls\\\\\\\": [],\\\\n        \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n        \\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"model\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"1973bdc0-ff05-4d8b-a341-f9b0202b2126\\\\\\\"\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_namespace\\\\\\\": [\\\\n        \\\\\\\"langchain_core\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"messages\\\\\\\"\\\\n      ],\\\\n      \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"1973bdc0-ff05-4d8b-a341-f9b0202b2126\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"model\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"{\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Great! So your solution focuses on bodyweight exercises and injury prevention. But I want to make sure we capture the FULL power of what you're offering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nYou've told me WHAT you do (bodyweight exercises, injury prevention), but I need to understand the deeper impact. Let me ask you this:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**How does this specifically address the two pain points your clients face?**\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. **The \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset** - How do bodyweight exercises and injury prevention help them overcome this psychological barrier? What results or confidence do they gain?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. **The beginner experience** - Why is bodyweight training + injury prevention the RIGHT approach for someone who's never been active? What makes them feel capable and successful?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nIn other words: What transformation or outcome do your clients experience? What can they DO or FEEL after working with you that they couldn't before?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"They realize they can do real strength training without needing a gym, which removes the intimidation factor and proves age doesn't matter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"They build strength safely without joint pain, so they actually stick with it and see results instead of getting injured and quitting\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"They gain confidence through small wins with bodyweight movements, which rebuilds their belief that they CAN get fit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n  ],\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"What's the real transformation or benefit your clients experience from your bodyweight + injury prevention approach?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"topics\\\\\\\": [\\\\n          \\\\\\\"audience\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"solution\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"idea\\\\\\\"\\\\n        ]\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"Great! So your solution focuses on bodyweight exercises and injury prevention. But I want to make sure we capture the FULL power of what you're offering.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou've told me WHAT you do (bodyweight exercises, injury prevention), but I need to understand the deeper impact. Let me ask you this:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n**How does this specifically address the two pain points your clients face?**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n1. **The \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"I'm too old\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" mindset** - How do bodyweight exercises and injury prevention help them overcome this psychological barrier? What results or confidence do they gain?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n2. **The beginner experience** - Why is bodyweight training + injury prevention the RIGHT approach for someone who's never been active? What makes them feel capable and successful?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn other words: What transformation or outcome do your clients experience? What can they DO or FEEL after working with you that they couldn't before?\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"examples\\\\\\\": [\\\\n          \\\\\\\"They realize they can do real strength training without needing a gym, which removes the intimidation factor and proves age doesn't matter\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"They build strength safely without joint pain, so they actually stick with it and see results instead of getting injured and quitting\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"They gain confidence through small wins with bodyweight movements, which rebuilds their belief that they CAN get fit\\\\\\\"\\\\n        ],\\\\n        \\\\\\\"conclusion\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"What's the real transformation or benefit your clients experience from your bodyweight + injury prevention approach?\\\\\\\"\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"ai\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"tool_calls\\\\\\\": [],\\\\n      \\\\\\\"invalid_tool_calls\\\\\\\": []\\\\n    },\\\\n    {\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_serializable\\\\\\\": true,\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I provide a 12-week progressive strength program with 3x/week 30-minute sessions focused on back and core-done via video coaching to accommodate busy schedules of men in their 50s.\\\\\\\\n        When a man in his 50s completes the program, he finally feels like himself again. He realizes he's not too old to get fit, and he's not too old to be healthy.\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n        \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n        \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"45ee6394-69e8-4a3e-b9ac-321d53370552\\\\\\\"\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"lc_namespace\\\\\\\": [\\\\n        \\\\\\\"langchain_core\\\\\\\",\\\\n        \\\\\\\"messages\\\\\\\"\\\\n      ],\\\\n      \\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"45ee6394-69e8-4a3e-b9ac-321d53370552\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"I provide a 12-week progressive strength program with 3x/week 30-minute sessions focused on back and core-done via video coaching to accommodate busy schedules of men in their 50s.\\\\\\\\n        When a man in his 50s completes the program, he finally feels like himself again. He realizes he's not too old to get fit, and he's not too old to be healthy.\\\\\\\",\\\\n      \\\\\\\"additional_kwargs\\\\\\\": {\\\\n        \\\\\\\"topics\\\\\\\": [\\\\n          \\\\\\\"audience\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"solution\\\\\\\",\\\\n          \\\\\\\"idea\\\\\\\"\\\\n        ]\\\\n      },\\\\n      \\\\\\\"response_metadata\\\\\\\": {},\\\\n      \\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"human\\\\\\\"\\\\n    }\\\\n  ]\\\\n}\\\"</message>\\n</chat-history>\\n        \\n        <task>\\n            Complete 1 of 3 tasks:\\n\\n            1. Explain the user's options to them\\n                - Use when: The user has just finished brainstorming\\n\\n            2. Answer any questions they may have about the process\\n                - Use when: The user has questions about the process\\n\\n            3. Call the finishedTool to automatically redirect to the website builder\\n                - Use when: The user has indicated they are ready to move on.\\n        </task>\\n\\n        <output>\\n            If outputting a response, use the following JSON schema:\\n\\n            Output JSON: {\\n                \\\"text\\\": \\\"Guide the user to the next step\\\",\\n                \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Option 1 explanation\\\", \\\"Option 2 explanation\\\"], // Optional, only if necessary\\n                \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Clearly state the next step\\\" // Optional, only if necessary\\n            }\\n        </output>\\n    \"}"
