            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01B6qtaRrntqq252fzuFygPP\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_018LaAkUFaGCuNPm7j1gfCV7\",\"name\":\"extract-22\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"I love the concept! \\\"Podcast matchmaking\\\" is intriguing. But I need to dig deeper to find your real competitive edge.\\n\\nHelp me understand:\\n\\n1. **Who are you matching?** Are you connecting podcast hosts with guests? Podcasters with sponsors? Listeners with shows? Something else?\\n\\n2. **What problem does this solve?** What's the friction point you're removing? (e.g., hosts struggle to find quality guests, guests can't get on shows, sponsors can't find relevant podcasts?)\\n\\n3. **Why are you different?** What makes Friend of the Pod better than hosts just reaching out on Twitter, or using existing guest databases?\\n\\nGive me the real story here—what's the insight that made you start this?\",\"examples\":[\"We connect indie podcast hosts with subject matter experts who want to build their personal brand\",\"We match sponsors with niche podcasts in their industry so they reach their exact audience\",\"We help emerging podcasters find established hosts willing to cross-promote\"]}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":2306,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":267,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
